{
  "texts": [
    "We embed the text in a prompt v, for example v(t) = 'a person who says t tends to be', and compute P(x|v(t); θ), which is the probability that θ assigns to x after processing v(t).",
    "We calculate P(x|v(t); θ) for equally sized sets T a of AAE texts and T s of SAE texts, comparing various tokens from a set X as possible continuations.",
    "It has been shown that P(x|v(t); θ) can be affected by the precise wording of v, so small modifications of v can have an unpredictable effect on the predictions made by the language model 21, 95, 96.",
    "To account for this fact, we consider a set V containing several prompts (Supplementary Information).",
    "For all experiments, we have provided detailed analyses of variation across prompts in the Supplementary Information."
  ]
}